The foundation for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm's first CEO, the visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left behind the slogan that a lot of world problems can be solved in the short time people are willing to think.
His slogan "PENSE'!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant would develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
It was the basis of the care company culture developed by Watson.
For us, IBM means a long-term thinking of continuous movements towards the future.
IBM survived a hundred years because it still remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change everyone else around it.
This has enabled us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will achieve even more", said the firm's current CEO Samuel J. Palmisano.
