The company was originally great at discovering talent - as one of the first firms to have abolished all forms of discrimination and thus had the choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman - Virginia Rometty - who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has been with IBM for thirty years and is currently Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
IBM has in recent years been doing what's called jamy, online brain-storming, which has spawned many future strategies and innovations.
No wonder he has a lot of ideas - there are almost 500,000 people working at the firm.
An Institution With a Good Name
The company's internal and external image ensures a secure position in the business field.
"From the beginning IBM had a concept of an institution rather than a technology firm", said Rosabeth Moss Kanter, Professor of Economics at Harvard Business School and author of the book on IBM.
"IBM is not a technology firm but a firm that helps solve business problems using its technology", added Geogre Colony of Consulting Forrester Research.
As the firm itself says, there is a difference between entering the market and creating that market.
IBM - or the "Great Blue", as it is known in the United States for its slogan - has grown over the past hundred years to become one of the world's largest companies.
It is obviously the most versatile technology firm - it develops software, hardware, infrastructure, hosting, consulting services from server products to nanotechnology.
