While researchers have well-defined guidelines on how to collect information other than through the Internet, there is a whole other thing online.
"I don't think a lot of users have ever thought about the fact that a researcher could study their profile", says Neil Selwyn, a sociologist at the London Knowledge Laboratory, according to a 2006 study he conducted by looking at his students' Facebook walls.
